content.description: Start on the sloping shelf and head left on small holds to a jug. Do a big move from the jug and head straight up.
content.location: Start shared by Tilted Earth, Driving Miss Daisy, and Archimedes' Lever.

content.description: Stand start to Toothpaste Highway. Start on the jug and make a big move straight up and out to a nonexistent hold on the lip. Top out above.
content.location: Start on jugs at head height about 7 feet left of the start to Tilted Earth.

content.description: Start as for Tilted Earth and pull out onto the flake. Instead of going up and left (Tilted), move right to a nano-crimp, then to some better crimps. Top out. Hard shit.

Under the right side of the roof, start on a sloping shelf, pull the roof into the thin flake, then go up on small holds and top out. 

  Other variations exist from these starting holds. Start here and traverse left under the roof, with different topouts. Ask around for more info, because many holds have broken and the names of different problems vary.
content.location: Right side of Axis Mundi Roof

content.description: Start on the sloping shelf of Tilted Earth, pull the roof, traverse left into a jug slot, then pull the rest of the roof straight up. Holds have broken, harder now?
content.location: Right side of the roof, exits to the left of Tilted Earth

content.description: Stand start in the center of the roof, at the jug slot on Driving Miss Daisy, and go straight up, finishing Driving Miss Daisy. Be careful not to fall and tumble down the banks of the river into Onion Creek lol. AKA Creek Dart.
content.protection: 1 or 2 pads, plus a spotter willing to stand under you as you both fall into the river lol.
content.location: Dead center of the Axis Mundi Roof

content.description: Start at the head height jugs shared by Toothpaste Dream and finish Archimedes' Lever.
content.location: 7 feet left of the start of Tilted Earth.

content.description: Same thing as Driving Miss Daisy: start on Tilted Earth, pull the roof, traverse left to jug, but then continue traversing left 5 more feet and exit straight out of the roof. Holds have broken, harder now?
content.location: Starts on the right of the roof, traverses left, and exits thru the center of the roof.

content.description: This is the giant, low roof on the far left of the McKinney bouldering bluff, left of Scrunchy wall. It's a beautiful thing, if only there were more problems on it.
